When you have a list of using statements inside the namespace declaration documented with a comment and you insert a new using statement using the "Ctrl+." feature, if the new statement is inserted at the top of the existing using statements, it will be inserted before the comment.

Using the following example:

namespace Fred.Bloggs
    {
        // Using statements
        using Newtonsoft.Json;

Inserting "using System;" results in:

namespace Fred.Bloggs
    {
        using System;
        // Using statements.
        using Newtonsoft.Json;

If you continue inserting using statements using the same mechanism without manually fixing the problem, all using statements that get inserted before (in this case) the "using Newtonsoft.Json;" statement, will also be inserted before the comment.

Inserting "using System.Diagnostics;" results in:

namespace Fred.Bloggs
    {
        using System;
        using System.Diagnostics;
        // Using statements.
        using Newtonsoft.Json;

I gave it a very quick check and the same problem does not seem to occur if the using statements are outside the namespace declaration.

This is a really minor, but, for me, annoying little bug.

