Hello, following the solution provided to the issue [#6984 ](https://github.com/dotnet/corert/issues/6984) , I tried playing around with the return of data structures from C++ to C#, as i couldn't find an issue related to this kind of operation, I thought about opening one in order to receive a few heads-up on the topic.


C++ Code
```
struct myStruct {
    int ok;
    string testStr;
} ;
extern "C" myStruct entry() {
    myStruct myStu;
    myStu.ok = 1;
    myStu.testStr = "hello";
    return myStu;
}
```

C# Code
```
namespace CppInterop
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            dynamic ok = entry();
        }
        [DllImport("*")]
        public extern static dynamic entry();
    }
}
```


As expected, i get this error
```
Unhandled Exception: System.Exception: Method '[CppInterop]CppInterop.Program.entry()' requires marshalling that is not yet supported by this compiler.
